EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES -- RETAIL LICENSES
***
1 This act would allow holders of a Class P license to purchase alcoholic beverages from
2 either a retail or wholesale establishment in the State of Rhode Island and allow wholesalers to
3 refuse to fulfill orders permitted under this section, or set minimum quantities or dollar values per
4 order. It would also permit caterers to serve and leave an event host's alcoholic beverages at their
5 residence so long as it is under the caterer's control for the entirety of the event.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
